mario.asm is a reverse engineering of the PRG data (only) of
the original Super Mario Bros., which comes from doppelganger.
It is "provided for your own use as-is." It's included here
under (at least) a claim of fair use:
  - It cannot be used to reproduce Super Mario Bros. without
    the graphics data from the game (and also requires some
    reformatting of the ROM that is not provided here)
  - Its use here is academic (model checking 6502 code)
    and substantially transformative, with many annotations
    and explanations added.

SMBDIS.ASM - A COMPREHENSIVE SUPER MARIO BROS. DISASSEMBLY
by doppelganger (doppelheathen@gmail.com)

This file is provided for your own use as-is. It will require the
character rom data and an iNES file header to get it to work.

